text: Fantastic and cute app. It can be as simple or complex as you want it to be!  I'm currently seeking out mental health treatment and was advised to try and keep track of any moods or changes while I explore a new medication. I found Daylio and it was just what I wanted and more!   You can set the time it asks, customize and add new activities. I really like this because I can keep track of any negative events I have and its easy to search by activity and bring up all instances. You can also add any notes for the day if you'd like.  Again, this is a fantastic app. You can be simple if you don't have much time or be really detailed as you like. Nice!

Am not the diary type but needed some easy way to track my activities and emotions. I also use the notes part to keep a simple record of my food intake (not interested in kcals) in relation to my moods. App is really easy to use with a fairly unobtrusive notification if you're not ready to log at the usual time. Like the way you can back up to Google drive too.

This app is so adorable!! It helped me track what I did to make my day "rad" and what happened to make it not so good. Not only that it also gives lots of statistics about how you are feeling which I think is very helpful, especially if you've been having a rough few days. It's also super simple to use, there are only five different pages and I learned how to use this app in just a few minutes!  I love the idea that you can add different activities to match you better, and the icons are so cute! I absolutely love this app and I hope everybody installs it!!

Wow, Daylio I am super impressed. The easiest most comprehensive and straight forward diary/journal app I have used. I am entirely loving this. The symbols to show what you're doing is exquisite, not to mention being able to choose another symbol not listed in the default and naming it. Just brilliant. You make journaling fun! And I actually use it several times a day as my mood changes. Great to keep track.

It's worth using this. Seriously. I have trouble doing things every day but my moods are so... changeable I had to do something, especially to determine whether or not I need mood stabilizers and to figure out what my triggers are. And an app as amazing as this somehow exists. It's worth buying (It's so cheap, and catch it on one of its 50% sales) and I have at least tracked down 1 trigger. It's so useful and simple and for someone who really struggles with visioning an app every day I use it flawlessly. It's reminders are simple and discreet, you don't have to open the app, it does most of the work for you.

Really dig this app! Been using it every day, several times a day. It's great.  If I could offer two suggestions, they would be: -The ability to mark which actions are considered positive, negative, or neutral (maybe three color-coding options?) -More action icons that depict negative actions (ie. two people yelling to depict an argument)

Simple, visual, effective! I've always liked the idea of daily journaling but felt that an entry everyday would get monotonous either to write or read back. But Daylio's smilies makes it quick and easy, and short responses are perfectly fine.

I really like that you can track multiple emotions throughout the day and what activities you were doing. It also tracks what emotions you typically log with what activities which is neat. And I like the graph of your ups and downs over the month. All around I really like this app. Is g the best one I've had for tracking this stuff. üëç üëç

This app is fantastic. I've been using it to learn more self awareness. As an autistic adult, I sometimes forget to check in with my needs. This app has been helping me track how all sorts of things alter my mood, from food to a knock on the door. Superb design, and ease of use.

I like the app, especially that it prompts me daily which has kept me on track. I really like being able to customize emotions. One thing I would like to see in a future update is the ability to rate the day on more than one scale. It would help me to be able to track more than one emotion/mood per day.

I really enjoy using this and purchased in full. I only wish it would sync with my iOS device rather than them being separate accounts/cloud storage. Oh and the export to CSV file is a horrid idea. It's unreadable. Why not a pdf format like Journey app?
replyText: Hey Comfy, thank you for your feedback and suggestions. We 100% agree and we plan to support .pdf format in the future. CSV file needs to be imported into some spreadsheet to have some use. We have a short tutorial that might help: http://daylio.helpscoutdocs.com/article/29-what-is-csv-and-how-it-looks Have a nice day!

text: Made my routine nicer, I can look at my days as something I can really do something about. And it became my personal journal. Incredible. It even helps me searching for bad mental triggers.  Great interface, has automatic backup ( pro version, which is cheap though)

I think this app does a good job of giving you a simple and concise medium to track your mood and journal a bit throughout the day.   It lets you tag activities you've done or are doing with a simple menu and you just write how you're feeling. If you're curious about how you've been feeling lately or if you're more stressed than usual, this app would make it easy to see what and when. Just answer the reminders and it works as advertised

I am just suggesting that you add an option to put some image on the my day or whatever you call it. Im not saying that its bad, im just suggesting... A diary/journal/story is more colorful with picture.... Still good job

Update: It would be great if the app also features adding photos in, because some days a picture is worth a thousand words! I love the fact that Daylio allows me to customize whatever activity I want  :") The even more lovely things is the streak encouragement and it doesn't have penalty, so it lessens the stress for me, making it easier for me to recall what happened during the day. I also love the app's calendar and summary function! Thanks to that, I know whatever that I did would make me feel better and vice versa.  One thing I think Should be a new function is when I look at the "You often do these things when you feel..." Is that it should allow you to go to whatever day it was that activity was found. Thus, making it even more nice and motivated!  Overall, this app is an amazing improvement to my life and I thank you all!

I have been using this app for, possibly 6-8 months in addition to learning to keep a physical bullet journal (paper and pen.) This app has helped me a LOT when I feel too tired or too out of it, or just plain forget, to update my physical bullet journal. It's cute, and I love the non intrusive banner ads instead of pop ups for the free version. I love the fact that I can keep track of anything, including moods. I really enjoy this app and I hope that if you are looking for an easy way to keep track of things, whatever they are, you check this out. <3

I like the daily promt to record my emotions, it is helpful to track them. tho i wish I had known that it cost money to unlock all the coolest features. I wanted too try a similar  iOS app and this seems to be the closest thing android has
This is literally the best app I've ever used. Beautiful design, doesn't get in the way, makes me actually WANT to use it. I will be very sad if they ever go out of business and turn off this app.
I really love this little app. It's surprisingly robust for as clean and simple as it comes across. I has really helped me track a variety of things and keep up a daily mini-journaling habit, too.

Easy to keep up. And you can write about your day if you want! Perfect way to get in the habit! I recommend this app for all who struggle with emotional clarity and pain. Tracking your mood is a great tool for recovery. Also or writers trying to write every day! Can't wait to graduate to an actual book journal!

Easy to use, but I wish the icons were sorted by subject and that there were more. I found there were not enough symbols based on educational subjects for my needs, had trouble indicating studying vs math class, etc. Some more generic symbols like üö´ ‚ÜóÔ∏è‚ÜñÔ∏è‚ÜòÔ∏è‚ÜôÔ∏è‚ñ∂Ô∏è‚è∏‚úñ‚úî‚ÅâÔ∏è‚ùóüè¥would be nice. Also there doesn't seem to be any truck symbols? üö´ over a cigarette would be would be useful for people who want to track days they didn't smoke. I bought the full version and appreciate being able to make custom moods.

This app is really great! Since I have so much to keep track of it's nice to have something that'll keep track of it for me. Even better, is that it'll remind me to submit multiple responses in a day. Another great thing is that it'll give like a "congrats on doing another day!" type thing and it makes me excited to keep track of my life!

Both useful and easy to use. Also, it's incredibly customizable, which is always a plus. I use it every day.  A suggestion, though--I would like a mechanism by which I could highlight significant entries for easy retrieval and review. I tend to write a lot, and having to go hunting for an entry I want to revisit is kind of a drag.

title: Can you get your entries back?
text: Can you get your entries back? ***THE MANUAL BACKUP AND RESTORE DOES NOT WORK*** I'm done with this app.                  My phone did a factory reset, I lost almost everything. One thing I lost, was 4+ months of entries. Is there anyway of getting these memories back? I have memory loss, I relied on these entries to remember. I had planned to write all the days down and see if I could remember anything, but I kept forgetting. I need these back
replyText: Hello Valerie, if you backed up your data you can simply install the app and go to Settings > Backup & Restore. We know that manual backup is annoying so we plan to include auto-backup in the future so people won't lost their memories. Have a nice day.

text: this app is brilliant! however, having paid for the app to have automatic backup, I didn't expect it to back up my entries over 40 times every day at midnight! is this a glitch, for it to be backing up so many times, each within a second or two of the last?

Overall good app., bit simplistic. Could be possible more affective if for each activity type there were a simple weighted scale, maybe 1-5. Over time it would provide a more refined view of cause and effect.

A simple way to really reflect and review how well you really think your day have been. No need for a journal or pen to bring along with you everywhere. Just bring this app in your phone. Helps you to really see the good habits you want to create and bad habits you want to kick. Hope I can unlock more amazing things in my life with this app by my side

This is a really easy way to keep track of my moods and keep my down days in perspectively. Really quick to log. Like the daily reminder too. More details can be added if desired. Only thing extra I'd like would be the ability to view more than just one calendar month, or say the past 6 weeks, on one graph.

I love this. Easy and helps my anxiety a bit just being able to quickly write down problems. Please don't update it is great the way it is. Every time I find an app I love an update happens and then it ruins the app for me... Please don't update this app it is amazing as is.

Easy to use and constant reminders are helpful. Tracks moods well and great graphing.  It would be good to have a button to check if going thru an episode like highly anxious, panic attack exteme low mood, high stress and identify trigger...

I love this app! This is also the first and only app I actually purchased because I found it extremely useful. I'm at 49 days in row right now. This app is so helpful in tracking your daily activities and moods. It's like a personal journal or diary and you can choose whether to write down how you're feeling or choose from a selection of moods and activities that take a quick 3 seconds to input. I love how you can write as much as you want and there is no limit. I love the selection of moods and how you can create any activities you want. I love how you can see your progress and refer back to days. It's also helpful for remembering what you did on a certain day. Three things that I could suggest for improvements are: adding more icons or symbols for activities and grouping them (so that we can create more specific activities - this is the most important suggestion that should be taken into consideration), having the ability to organize activities in the same way that you select them (so organizing them in the form of the bubbles that you choose instead of seeing them as a list - I ask this because I like to group similar activities easily and in the list view, it is more difficult to do) and to be able to tap the date and hide all the activities and moods that happened that day (so when I try to search an activity, I don't have to scan everything that happened in each day that shows up under that search). Even without these suggestions, the app is still awesome and I have to thank every single person who worked to develop this app. You have made my life so much better!

I've been using Daylio for about 3 weeks now, and I've enjoyed filling out the daily diary entries. Downloaded it thinking the quick emoticon answers were a great idea and a nice way to get over the "can't be bothered writing" barrier I normally hit with diaries, but I've actually found myself using the quick notes nearly every day as well.  I've only used the simple displays for analytics so far as I don't have much data, but I'm keen to see what I can do with it a few months down the line. Would recommend for anyone who's look to capture their moods and daily activities without investing much time or energy, very well designed.

A simple way to track my impressions of my day-to-day activities and moods. Everyday at 8P I check in to see if I am satisfied with how I directed my day. I would like to have more emoji options, but I think that is unlocked in the paid version. I also had bugs with my cloud backup.  So, not sure what happens if I change devices for long term data analysis.

Always reminds me and let's me have to reminders in case I loose interest or forgot. I now have a great account of my life and I really enjoy reading back at my entries and have been using it for 208 consecutive days

Great customer service. Heartbroken when I swapped phones and lost 416 days entries, and my premium, but Stephan patiently kept emailing me til we figured out where I'd gone wrong. I love my Daylio!!!

This is a great app if you want to see what activities regularly make your mood high or low. It can even be used to spot activities that may trigger your anxiety or depression if you suffer with mental health

I love everything except for the fact that if I try to update after midnight I can't update for the day that I am trying to track. I try to update before bed so I can account for the entire day but sometimes I stay up late depending on my work schedule, whether or not I go out, etc. I get that you like to give a sense of being rewarded by being like HEY YOU UPDATED THIS MANY DAYS IN A ROW but sometimes I can't get to my phone earlier. I love this app and even paid for the premium but I might have to switch to a different app just because of this feature because I use this app for health reasons.
This app is easy to use, intuitive, customizable, and doesn't get in your way. This has helped me track down what foods and activities are causing health issues in my life. Thank you!
Emojis are a bit cutesy for my taste, generally. But these simple graphics just work when summing up a day. Day was a rollercoaster of emotions? Make multiple entries. Love the statistical summaries.

This is a very nice app. It definitely needs to be able to sync across devices though. Also, it would be good (i) if there was a 'today' button to return to today's date after looking at previous days (ii) if we could add entries for past dates by simply clicking on a date in the calendar rather than having to scroll through years and months each time (iii) if the daily reminder wouldn't appear if we've already entered data for today
